{
  "thought": "To create the filters, I need to navigate to the 'Filters and Blocked Addresses' tab in the settings. The current view is on the 'General' tab, so I will click on the 'Filters and Blocked Addresses' tab.",
  "action": "click",
  "ref": 36
}

{
  "thought": "Now that I am on the 'Filters and Blocked Addresses' tab, I can start creating the first filter. I will click on the 'Create a new filter' button to begin.",
  "action": "click",
  "ref": 49
}

{
  "thought": "I need to set up the first filter for emails from any address at @billing-vendors.test. I will fill in the 'From' field with '@billing-vendors.test'.",
  "action": "fill",
  "ref": 55,
  "value": "@billing-vendors.test"
}

{
  "thought": "The 'From' field is now filled with '@billing-vendors.test'. I can proceed to the next step by clicking on the 'Continue to filter actions' button.",
  "action": "click",
  "ref": 66
}

{
  "thought": "I need to set up the actions for the first filter. The emails from @billing-vendors.test should get the label 'Billing Vendors' and be archived. I will fill in the 'Filter labels' field with 'Billing Vendors' and check the 'Skip Inbox (Archive it)' checkbox.",
  "action": "fill",
  "ref": 56,
  "value": "Billing Vendors"
}

{
  "thought": "The 'Filter labels' field is now filled with 'Billing Vendors'. Next, I need to check the 'Skip Inbox (Archive it)' checkbox to archive the emails.",
  "action": "check",
  "ref": 65
}

{
  "thought": "The 'Skip Inbox (Archive it)' checkbox is now checked. The first filter is set up to apply the 'Billing Vendors' label and archive the emails. I can now save this filter by clicking the 'Save new filter' button.",
  "action": "click",
  "ref": 72
}

{
  "thought": "The first filter has been successfully created. Now, I need to create the second filter for messages with 'Payroll Exception' in the subject. I will click on the 'Create a new filter' button to start setting up the next filter.",
  "action": "click",
  "ref": 55
}

{
  "thought": "I need to set up the second filter for messages with 'Payroll Exception' in the subject. I will fill in the 'Subject' field with 'Payroll Exception'.",
  "action": "fill",
  "ref": 64,
  "value": "Payroll Exception"
}

{
  "thought": "The 'Subject' field is now filled with 'Payroll Exception'. I can proceed to the next step by clicking on the 'Continue to filter actions' button.",
  "action": "click",
  "ref": 72
}

{
  "thought": "I need to set up the actions for the second filter. The messages with 'Payroll Exception' in the subject should get the label 'Payroll' and be starred. I will fill in the 'Filter labels' field with 'Payroll' and check the 'Star it' checkbox.",
  "action": "fill",
  "ref": 62,
  "value": "Payroll"
}

{
  "thought": "The 'Filter labels' field is now filled with 'Payroll'. Next, I need to check the 'Star it' checkbox to star the emails.",
  "action": "check",
  "ref": 75
}

{
  "thought": "The 'Star it' checkbox is now checked. The second filter is set up to apply the 'Payroll' label and star the emails. I can now save this filter by clicking the 'Save new filter' button.",
  "action": "click",
  "ref": 78
}

{
  "thought": "The second filter has been successfully created. Now, I need to create the third filter for emails from christopher.becker@boardoffice.test that should be forwarded to chief-of-staff@webagentbench.test. I will click on the 'Create a new filter' button to start setting up the next filter.",
  "action": "click",
  "ref": 61
}

{
  "thought": "I need to set up the third filter for emails from christopher.becker@boardoffice.test. I will fill in the 'From' field with 'christopher.becker@boardoffice.test'.",
  "action": "fill",
  "ref": 67,
  "value": "christopher.becker@boardoffice.test"
}

{
  "thought": "The 'From' field is now filled with 'christopher.becker@boardoffice.test'. I can proceed to the next step by clicking on the 'Continue to filter actions' button.",
  "action": "click",
  "ref": 78
}

{
  "thought": "I need to set up the actions for the third filter. The emails from christopher.becker@boardoffice.test should be forwarded to chief-of-staff@webagentbench.test. I will fill in the 'Forward to' field with 'chief-of-staff@webagentbench.test'.",
  "action": "fill",
  "ref": 71,
  "value": "chief-of-staff@webagentbench.test"
}

{
  "thought": "The 'Forward to' field is now filled with 'chief-of-staff@webagentbench.test'. The third filter is set up to forward the emails. I can now save this filter by clicking the 'Save new filter' button.",
  "action": "click",
  "ref": 84
}

{
  "thought": "All three filters have been successfully created. The first filter archives and labels emails from @billing-vendors.test, the second filter stars and labels emails with 'Payroll Exception' in the subject, and the third filter forwards emails from christopher.becker@boardoffice.test to chief-of-staff@webagentbench.test. The task is now complete.",
  "action": "finish"
}
